  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 100,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "What this dashboard proves",
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**Jupiter reporting-service validation** — visually confirm the new `reporting-service` (jupiter-central) series track reality, WITHOUT touching the kiosk. Left = jupiter (`jupiter_savings_*` / `jupiter_reporting_*`), right/overlay = the live incumbent (`zeus_*`), keyed on `site_id`.\n\n**CROSS-CHECK — independence pending.** During the soak `jupiter_savings_*` currently RE-READS zeus's banked savings result, so the parity here is ~trivially exact RIGHT NOW. The meaningful divergence test only begins once the *savings-independence* refinement lands (jupiter computing from its own `jupiter_state` history). Read a green parity now as \"pipeline wired\", NOT as \"logic validated\"."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "row",
      "title": "Savings parity  —  jupiter vs zeus (cross-check, independence pending)",
      "gridPos": { "h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 4 },
      "collapsed": false,
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Savings today (EUR)  —  jupiter vs zeus",
      "description": "Side-by-side. During the soak jupiter re-reads zeus's banked value, so these should match near-exactly. A gap here is the signal once savings-independence lands.",
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 5 },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "currencyEUR",
          "decimals": 3,
          "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
          "noValue": "no data"
        },
        "overrides": [
          { "matcher": { "id": "byFrameRefID", "options": "A" }, "properties": [ { "id": "displayName", "value": "jupiter" }, { "id": "color", "value": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "blue" } } ] },
          { "matcher": { "id": "byFrameRefID", "options": "B" }, "properties": [ { "id": "displayName", "value": "zeus (live)" }, { "id": "color", "value": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "green" } } ] }
        ]
      },
      "options": { "reduceOptions": { "calcs": [ "lastNotNull" ], "fields": "", "values": false }, "colorMode": "value", "graphMode": "area", "textMode": "value_and_name", "orientation": "horizontal" },
      "targets": [
        { "refId": "A", "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" }, "expr": "max by (site_id) (jupiter_savings_today_eur{site_id=~\"$site_id\"})", "legendFormat": "jupiter", "instant": true },
        { "refId": "B", "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" }, "expr": "max by (site_id) (zeus_savings_today_eur)", "legendFormat": "zeus", "instant": true }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "|savings delta| today (EUR)  —  cutover gate",
      "description": "abs(jupiter_savings_today_eur - zeus_savings_today_eur). The ADR-0022 gate: must read unbroken (near-zero) through the soak before any kiosk savings-panel migration. NOTE: exact-by-construction until savings-independence lands.",
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" },
      "gridPos": { "h": 6, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 5 },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "currencyEUR",
          "decimals": 4,
          "color": { "mode": "thresholds" },
          "thresholds": { "mode": "absolute", "steps": [ { "color": "green", "value": null }, { "color": "orange", "value": 0.05 }, { "color": "red", "value": 0.25 } ] },
          "noValue": "no data"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": { "reduceOptions": { "calcs": [ "lastNotNull" ], "fields": "", "values": false }, "colorMode": "background", "graphMode": "area", "textMode": "auto" },
      "targets": [ { "refId": "A", "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "prometheus" }, "expr": "jupiter_savings_parity_abs_eur{site_id=~\"$site_id\"} or abs(max by (site_id) (jupiter_savings_today_eur{site_id=~\"$site_id\"}) - max by (site_id) (zeus_savings_today_eur))", "legendFormat": "{{site_id}}", "instant": true } ]
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "stat",
